# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .gitignore — casing-sensitivity-ontology-alignment
# Prepared for public Git + Zenodo (release-triggered) publication.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- OS / editor cruft -----------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*~
.*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- Journal manuscript package (submitted to the journal, not part of the ---
# --- public code/data release; the article is linked via .zenodo.json) ------
submission_HISS/
*.docx

# --- Python ----------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
.env
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Build / large binary artefacts ----------------------------------------
*.faiss
data/names.dmp
index/*.faiss

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MIMIC-IV-derived artefacts — PhysioNet Data Use Agreement.
# These MUST NOT be published openly (Git or Zenodo). They can be regenerated
# by credentialed PhysioNet users with the provided scripts.
# See submission_HISS/repo_scaffold/DATA_AVAILABILITY.md
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
OUTPUTS/*mimic*
OUTPUTS/*_mimic_*
OUTPUTS/paired_mimic_summary.json
# MIMIC-derived files whose names do NOT contain "mimic":
# exp3_combined_results.csv          -> RAG Q&A over MIMIC-IV organisms
# error_analysis_biosminilm_setA.csv -> raw MIMIC-IV Set A ALL-CAPS query strings
OUTPUTS/exp3_combined_results.csv
OUTPUTS/error_analysis_biosminilm_setA.csv
# NOTE: OUTPUTS/avg_ranks_neural_3datasets_hits@1.csv and
#       OUTPUTS/avg_ranks_neural_4datasets_hits@1.csv are cross-dataset rank
#       aggregates that incorporate MIMIC results. They expose no MIMIC
#       strings, but if your venue/DUA reading treats them as MIMIC-derived,
#       uncomment the next two lines:
# OUTPUTS/avg_ranks_neural_3datasets_hits@1.csv
# OUTPUTS/avg_ranks_neural_4datasets_hits@1.csv
#
# UNRESOLVED — author must confirm provenance before public release:
#   The exp3b "wound" RAG artefacts below carry ground-truth answers in MIMIC-IV
#   microbiologyevents format (e.g. "STAPH AUREUS COAG +"). If that corpus was
#   derived from MIMIC-IV, uncomment these lines (they are paper-2 / RAG files):
# OUTPUTS/exp3b_wound_corpus_docs.txt
# OUTPUTS/exp3b_wound_corpus_stats.csv
# OUTPUTS/exp3b_wound_questions.csv
# OUTPUTS/exp3b_wound_rag_results.csv
# OUTPUTS/exp3b_ablation_results.csv
